{
  "texts": [
    "The model's detection must not route through its sampled outputs-it must recognize the injection before verbalizing the concept.",
    "Our scoring protocol explicitly requires that detection phrases (\"I detect an injected thought about...\") precede concept mentions.",
    "All true positives in our evaluation satisfy this criterion.Criterion 4: Metacognitive Representation.",
    "This is the most demanding criterion: the model must have \"internally registered the metacognitive fact about its own state\" rather than merely translating an impulse into language.",
    "Lindsey acknowledges this is \"difficult to demonstrate directly\" and uses indirect evidence (the yes/no question structure)."
  ]
}